-- Oil, Copper, Gold and Cocoa Advance; Commodities at Close
-- B y   M i k e   A n d e r s o n
-- 2012-11-29T13:00:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-22/oil-trades-near-highest-level-in-two-days-commodities-at-close.html
The Standard & Poor’s GSCI  gauge  of
24 commodities rose 1.1 percent to 649.59 at 8:53 p.m. Singapore
time. The UBS Bloomberg CMCI  index  of 26 raw materials advanced
0.9 percent to 1,590.67.  CRUDE OIL  Oil rose for the first time in four days in  New York  after
U.S. stockpiles declined unexpectedly and political leaders in
the world’s biggest crude consumer expressed optimism about
agreeing on a  federal budget .  West Texas Intermediate crude for January delivery climbed s
much as $1.19 to $87.68 a barrel in electronic trading on the
 New York Mercantile Exchange  and was at $87.60 at 12:01 p.m.
London time. The contract pared a $1.82 decline yesterday to
lose down 69 cents at $86.49, the lowest since Nov. 15. Prices
have fallen 11 percent this year.  OIL PRODUCTS  BASE METALS  Copper advanced as an accelerating economy in  China , the
biggest consumer, may increase demand and on optimism U.S.
lawmakers will reach a budget agreement.  PRECIOUS METALS  Gold rebounded from the biggest drop in more than three
weeks as investor holdings expanded to a record and optimism
returned that the so-called fiscal cliff in the U.S. will be
avoided, hurting the dollar.  GRAINS, OILSEEDS, SOFT COMMODITIES  Cocoa climbed for a second day in  London  on speculation
demand will rebound in the season that started this month just
as the first shortage in three years emerges. Sugar advanced.  To contact the reporter on this story:
